  "text": "Because TBR1 was shown to directly regulate the expression of Grin2b [CITATION_1] , one of the NMDAR subunits implicated in proper neuronal activity, and because the GRIN2B expression levels were upregulated upon behavioral stimulation [CITATION_2] , we then assessed whether the activitydependent upregulation of Tbr1 expression is relevant to the Frontiers in Cellular Neuroscience www.frontiersin.org vehicle (Ctrl) for 6 h. Immediately (0 h) or 12 more hours (12 h) after treatment, neurons were harvested for quantitative-PCR using Cyp as an internal control to quantify the relative mRNA levels of Tbr1 and Grin2b at 21 DIV. The experiments were performed independently at least three times. Data are presented as the mean ± SEM. *P < 0.05; **P < 0.001; ***P < 0.001; n.s., not significant.",
